[Staged reading of ‘Fundraiser’](https://www.madhorse.com/)
---

7:30 p.m. Saturday. Mad Horse Theatre, 24 Mosher St., South Portland, pay-what-you-can tickets available at the door and after the reading. [madhorse.com](https://www.madhorse.com/).

Mad Horse Theatre presents a staged reading of a play by company member Brent Askari. “Fundraiser” is a comedy of questionable manners centered on two couples attending a school fundraiser together. Vaulted secrets are spilled during 90 minutes of sharp-witted dialogue. The readers are company members Joe Bearor, Marie Stewart Harmon and Nick Schroeder, along with guest artist Casey Turner.

[Dueling Pianos](https://francocenter.org/event/dueling-pianos-laughs-dancing-fun-jan-24/)
---

[![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/0122-AmyThomason-dueling-pianos.jpg?w=300)](https://w2pcms.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2026/01/0122-AmyThomason-dueling-pianos.jpg)

Pianist Amy Thomason. (Photo courtesy of the Franco Center)

[![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/01222-BillyWard-dueling-pianos.jpg?w=300)](https://w2pcms.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2026/01/01222-BillyWard-dueling-pianos.jpg)

Pianist Billy Ward. (Photo courtesy of Billy Ward)

7 p.m. Saturday. Franco Center, 46 Cedar St., Lewiston, $25 in advance, $30 at the door. [francocenter.org](https://francocenter.org/event/dueling-pianos-laughs-dancing-fun-jan-24/).

For an invigorating night of classic rock, pop hits, throwback oldies and audience requests, head to the Franco Center’s lower level lounge for Dueling Pianos. Pianists Amy Thomason and Billy Ward will be tickling 176 keys during a performance that’s been brought back to the Franco Center by popular demand.

‘[Forbidden Broadway: Merrily We Stole a Song](https://sanfordpac.org/forbidden-broadway-2/)‘
---

7 p.m. Saturday. Sanford Performing Arts Center, 100 Alumni Blvd., Sanford, $31-$54. [sanfordpac.org](https://sanfordpac.org/forbidden-broadway-2/).

[![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/0122-Forbidden-Broadway.jpg)](https://w2pcms.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/10/2026/01/0122-Forbidden-Broadway.jpg)

Cast members in a scene from “Forbidden Broadway: Merrily We Stole a Song.” (Photo courtesy of Sanford Performing Arts Center)

For a sassy, satirical night of Broadway tunes with a hilarious twist, head to Sanford. “Forbidden Broadway: Merrily We Stole a Song” is a new version of a long-running musical roast of songs from “The Outsiders,” “Phantom of the Opera,” “Wicked” and “Six,” among several others. All told, 31 musicals are skewered over the course of a 90-minute musical extravaganza.

